This paper discusses a game model for security systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The model is based on game theory (cs.GT) and involves interactions between users and network administrators, which can be modeled using stochastic games with imperfect information. The use of sensors to detect the state of the system suggests a potential application of machine learning or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the possibility of collaborations between attackers, which could fall under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). Finally, the paper presents a numerical simulation, which could be considered a form of computational science (cs.SI).
